    "baseball_pulse": "MY TEAM\nThere is no relevant news for your roster today.\n\nMY PROSPECTS\nNo prospect news today.\n\nAROUND THE LEAGUE\nSpencer Strider will activate from the injured list on Sunday for the Braves, giving Atlanta another ace in their rotation after their dominant start. The Red Sox placed Garrett Crochet on the injured list with a shoulder issue, creating offensive pressure down the stretch. Trevor Rogers was placed on the injured list by the Orioles due to illness, while the Tigers moved both Casey Mize and Javier B\u00e1ez to the IL. Several notable designations for assignment included Tommy Pham, Eloy Jim\u00e9nez, Joey Lucchesi, Carlos Carrasco, and Randal Grichuk, as clubs made roster adjustments.\n\nBASEBALL TODAY\nThe Atlanta Braves remain scorching hot at 22-9 after Matt Olson's walk-off homer secured another series victory, extending their streak to nine series without a loss. The Arizona Diamondbacks powered four homers past the Brewers with Ketel Marte and Corbin Carroll going back-to-back in the ninth, while Hunter Goodman launched two homers to lead the Rockies to victory. Nathan Church robbed a would-be walk-off homer to secure a Cardinals win in a thrilling defensive moment.",
